This paper discusses the security problems associated with the customization process in the Android ecosystem, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also utilizes game theory concepts to model the competition between vendors, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of regulation on the Android ecosystem, which falls under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of security-conscious consumers on the market, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
